sql:
SELECT credential_name
FROM credentials
WHERE credential_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM graduates
WHERE credential_id = 1;

SELECT name
FROM graduates
WHERE graduate_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Credential types refer to different levels or kinds of educational certifications or diplomas (e.g., Certificate, Associate, Bachelor's, Master's); 
- Median income refers to the middle value in the range of all incomes; 
- The duration of a credential program is the length of time it takes to complete the program.

